    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ORMs (Object-Relational Mappers) map Python classes to database tables, generating SQL from method calls. SQLAlchemy and Django ORM reduce boilerplate for agent persistence — sessions, runs, users — while supporting migrations, relationships, and async queries in modern FastAPI services."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You define models as Python classes; ORM translates "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "session.add(run)",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to INSERT. Relationships express foreign keys: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Run.tool_events",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " loads related rows. SQLAlchemy 2.0 supports async sessions with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "AsyncSession",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and explicit "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "select()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " statements."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from sqlalchemy.orm import DeclarativeBase, Mapped, mapped_column, relationship\nfrom sqlalchemy import String, ForeignKey\nfrom uuid import UUID, uuid4\n\nclass Base(DeclarativeBase):\n    pass\n\nclass Run(Base):\n    __tablename__ = \"runs\"\n    id: Mapped[UUID] = mapped_column(primary_key=True, default=uuid4)\n    status: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String(32))\n    session_id: Mapped[UUID] = mapped_column(ForeignKey(\"sessions.id\"))\n    tool_events: Mapped[list[\"ToolEvent\"]] = relationship(back_populates=\"run\")\n\nclass ToolEvent(Base):\n    __tablename__ = \"tool_events\"\n    id: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(primary_key=True, autoincrement=True)\n    run_id: Mapped[UUID] = mapped_column(ForeignKey(\"runs.id\"))\n    tool_name: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String(64))\n    run: Mapped[Run] = relationship(back_populates=\"tool_events\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Raw SQL everywhere slows feature work and invites SQL injection if concatenated strings slip in. ORMs provide parameterized queries, model-centric code aligned with Pydantic API layers, and migration integration — agent teams ship run tracking faster with fewer data bugs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Productivity",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — CRUD without handwritten SQL"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Safety",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — bound parameters by default"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Relationships",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — navigate run.tool_events in Python"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Async support",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — SQLAlchemy async for FastAPI"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ecosystem",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — Alembic migrations, SQLModel Pydantic hybrid"
                  }
